caption: I love this place!! Good good crab legs and my friend had the ribs and we also had the smoke wings.. Awesome delicious.

We sampled each other’s varied dishes such as the catfish, fried chicken, appetizers, seafood dishes and a variety of meats, each dish was consistently bland, dry and offensive to the palate.  The price points charged are not commensurate with the quality of the dishes.  In other words, the prices are way too high and the quality of the food is way too low.  Of note, the gumbo was average, not offensive.  This establishment is struggling and unless something changes quickly, stick a fork in this place.

I went to Porkchop in Hyde Park with a few friends with high expectations for the experience. Porkchop is always being recommended to me so I knew this was my chance to see what the hype was about. I was disappointed. The Porkchop in Hyde park is a combination of two restaurants, Porkchop and bleu fish. This is strange from the get go, but I rolled with it. The issue though is that the menu is overloaded with items so it took us a solid fifteen minutes to get through the menu and figure out what we were going to order. Porkchop is a bbq restaurant and bleu fish is a fish and steak restaurant. So going through the menu you have to decide what you really want to eat but everything is together. Additionally, so many items are market price that you are confronted with decision fatigue by the time you are ordering.  The service itself was okay. There was only one other table of people so...we got attention though usually at inopportune times.  As for the food, it was...okay. My husband and I shared a full slab of ribs, lobster Mac and cheese, and Brussels sprouts. It tasted good, but by no means the "best". The Brussel sprouts were not good and I don't recommend them.  My friends enjoyed their food: bacon wrapped dates, cheese fries, cornbread.  The plus side is that there are plenty of options but the downside is that there may be too many options so they don't do one thing well.

The rice was like the boil in the bag.  We did eat the Shrimp because we both were very hungry.  She asked if we wanted anything else my friend said no and I said I would try the brisket.   They came out with a sample to see if I liked it.  It was horrible.  My friend and I just ate the bread and I finished off my coleslaw.   Then the waitress came over to tell us that they were going to take half off of our entrees and that was it.  My friend and I just said  it's ok because we wouldn't be back.  We both thought that the manager should have come over to explain the bill.  Poor management skills. And now we see why the place was empty and all the other restaurants in the area was crowded.    Will not ever go back there again!!!!
